# Code repo memory-bank

When working inside **Gynasium** or **GymnasiumTwo**, use that repo’s **`memory-bank/`** (see `context_dir` in `registry/projects.yaml`).

## Read tiers

| When | Read |
|------|------|
| Every task in a code repo | `memory-bank/activeContext.md`, `memory-bank/progress.md` |
| Task targets one environment (e.g. `freeway/`, `bipedal_walker/`) | That env’s `memory-bank/environments/<name>/activeContext.md` and `progress.md` |
| New env, large refactor, or user says **update memory bank** | Full top-level set (`projectbrief`, `productContext`, `systemPatterns`, `techContext`) plus relevant `environments/<name>/` |

## Write tiers (required after substantive work)

- Update `activeContext.md` and `progress.md` (repo and env level as applicable).
- Record experiments in env `approaches.md`; patterns in `systemPatterns.md` / `techContext.md` when they change.

## Layout rules (from registry)

- **Gynasium (`per_env_self_contained`):** code and helpers under `<env>/`; data under `data/<env>/`. Avoid depending on other env folders.
- **GymnasiumTwo (`shared_common`):** shared logic in `common/`; per-game code in `pong/`, `freeway/`; data under `data/<game>/`.

Agents **must** edit memory-bank files directly in the repo (no MCP-only restriction).
